In this speech delivered at the Walter E. Washington Convention Center, President Joe Biden addresses the Congressional Hispanic Caucus and discusses various topics including the achievements of his administration, the American Rescue Plan, the Inflation Reduction Act, infrastructure, climate change, immigration, gun safety, and the importance of unity and progress in the United States. He emphasizes the need for bipartisan cooperation and expresses optimism for the future of the country. The President also acknowledges the contributions and challenges faced by Hispanic Americans and promises continued support for their communities.